@node part1.1 "System Requirements..."
@toc "Main"
@{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}System Requirements:
@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}
For FinalCalc to operate, it requires the following:

At least 3 megabytes of RAM (random access memory) in your system, with at
least 2 megabytes of free RAM when FinalCalc is run.

AmigaOS (Amiga Operating System) version 2.0 or higher.  FinalCalc will run
under versions 1.2 and 1.3 of AmigaOS, but with reduced functionality.

A hard disk with at least 5 megabytes of free space.

FinalCalc uses several system libraries.  The AmigaGuide system library and
the ARexx libraries are needed for all features of FinalCalc to be available.
@endnode


@node part1.2 "Running & Quitting FinalCalc..."
@toc "Main"
@{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}Running FinalCalc from the Workbench:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}
To run FinalCalc from the Workbench, simply double-click its icon.  FinalCalc
will start up and show you a blank project.

You can also run FinalCalc from a project's icon.  When FinalCalc saves a
project, it creates an icon for that project.  If you double-click on the
project's icon, FinalCalc will start up and load that project immediately.

@{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}Running FinalCalc from the Shell:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}
To run FinalCalc from the command shell, change to the FinalCalc: directory,
and then simply type the name of the program.  (either FinalCalc or
FinalCalc.FPU)  The current shell must have a minimum stack of 20480 bytes for
FinalCalc to operate correctly.

@{b}@{u}@{fg highlight}Quitting FinalCalc:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}
To quit FinalCalc, use the 'Project - Quit' menu.  This will close the current
project.  When you close all projects active in FinalCalc, you will be asked
whether you want to quit the program.  If you click on the 'Quit' button,
FinalCalc will shut down.
@next "FinalCalc:guide/part2.guide/Main"
@endnode
